-- Ready set: { spec-excerpt, awkward-program }
-- Pick: spec-excerpt (arbitrary вҖ” both are independent)

вҠў spec-excerpt
  yield text

  вҠў= text вҶҗ "## Cell v0.1 Spec вҖ” Key Constraints

Cells declare inputs with `given` and outputs with `yield`.
All inputs must be fully bound before evaluation.
There is no conditional `given` вҖ” every declared input is required.
There is no branching construct вҖ” cells execute linearly by data dependency.
There is no `try/fallback` pattern вҖ” oracle failure (вҠЁ?) is the only recovery.
There is no way to express 'evaluate A, then choose B or C based on result.'
There is no guard clause on cells вҖ” a cell cannot say 'only run me if X.'
Versioning of evolved cells uses prime marks: cell, cell', cell''.

Open Questions from v0.1:
1. Error handling вҖ” what when вҠў= throws or вҲҙ produces wrong type?
2. Versioning beyond prime marks вҖ” В§cell''' doesn't scale.
3. Streaming вҖ” need ~ annotation for incremental input.
4. Oracle distinction вҖ” assert vs rule, soft vs hard preconditions."

-- eval-one: вҠў= deterministic. text вҶҗ string literal. No LLM needed.

  yield text вүЎ "## Cell v0.1 Spec вҖ” Key Constraints ..."

