вҠў propose-spec-change
  given identify-awkwardnessвҶ’problems вүЎ [{quote: "handle-toxic...", ...}, ...]
  given identify-awkwardnessвҶ’root-causes вүЎ ["RC1: No automatic 'select non-вҠҘ' combinator...", "RC2: No wildcard over guard-gated cells...", "RC3: No case-dispatch grouping..."]
  given spec-excerptвҶ’text вүЎ "## Cell v0.1 Spec вҖ” Key Constraints ..."
  yield proposed-syntax, rationale, compatibility-analysis

  вҲҙ For each root cause, propose a concrete syntax addition or change...

-- LLM evaluation:

  yield proposed-syntax вүЎ "## Proposed Syntax Additions

### 1. Wildcard over guard-gated cells (addresses RC1 + RC2)

No new syntax needed вҖ” v0.2 wildcard deps (`given handler-*вҶ’output`) combined
with guard-induced вҠҘ and given? already solve this. The merge cell becomes:

```
вҠў merge-result
  given? handler-*вҶ’output    -- wildcard collects from all handler-* cells
  given classifyвҶ’label
  yield final-output

  вҲҙ Select the non-вҠҘ output from В«handler-*вҶ’outputВ».
```

This requires RENAMING the handlers to share a prefix (handle-toxic вҶ’ handler-toxic,
etc.) so the wildcard pattern matches. The wildcard resolves to an array; exactly
one element is non-вҠҘ due to mutually exclusive guards.

### 2. Case-dispatch grouping (addresses RC3) вҖ” DEFERRED

A `вҠў handle | classifyвҶ’label` pattern-match syntax would group variant cells
under a single declaration. This is a larger change. The guard+wildcard pattern
from (1) achieves 80% of the benefit with zero new syntax. Case-dispatch is
worth exploring in v0.3 but is NOT minimal for v0.2."

  yield rationale вүЎ "RC1 (no 'select non-вҠҘ' combinator): Solved by wildcard deps + given?. The wildcard collects an array of handler outputs. Exactly one is non-вҠҘ due to mutually exclusive guards. The вҲҙ body says 'pick the non-вҠҘ one.' This is composable вҖ” adding a 4th handler requires only adding the handler cell with the right prefix. merge-result does not change.

RC2 (no wildcard over guard-gated cells): Solved by the same mechanism. Wildcard deps already exist in v0.2. Guard-induced вҠҘ already propagates. given? already accepts вҠҘ. The three features compose without any new syntax.

RC3 (no case-dispatch grouping): Deferred to v0.3. The guard+wildcard pattern eliminates the O(N) maintenance problem (RC2) and the coordination problem (RC1). The remaining awkwardness вҖ” routing logic scattered across cell headers вҖ” is severity 2, not a fundamental limitation. Case-dispatch would be elegant but is not minimal."

  yield compatibility-analysis вүЎ "No new syntax introduced. All features used (wildcard deps, guard clauses, given?, вҠҘ propagation) are already in v0.2. The only change is structural: rename handler cells to share a prefix (handle-* pattern). This is a refactoring recommendation, not a spec change. Zero backward compatibility concerns."

